In retrospect it strikes me that even aside from the many technical
hurdles that arise,  there is a simple reason that air-breathing SSTO
doesn't make much sense.  The whole advantage of an air-breathing
vehicle is that it need not lift the oxygen that it consumes.  But
unfortunately, the vehicle must still accelerate the oxygen (possibly
along with a lot of nitrogen).  Reaching LEO entails increasing
specific gravitational potential energy by about 2 MJ/kg and specific
kinetic energy by about 25 MJ/kg.  Therefore, eliminating the need to
lift the oxygen contributes little to the energy budget.
